def sum_of_weigths(X, w):
    return X.dot(w)

def activation(x):
    a = 1 / (1 + np.exp(-x))
    return a

train, y dn ; ploting visual

dict_of_w = {}
res_dict = {}

def train(w, real = y, i = 0):
    global dict_of, list_of
    pred = activation(sum_of_weigths(x, w))
    delta = x * pred * (1 - pred) * (real - pred) #   
    new_w = w + delta #  
        
    dict_of_w[i] = new_w #     dict,   -   
    res_dict[pred] = abs((real - pred)/real) #       
    
    if abs((real - pred)/real) > dd: #  
        train(new_w, i = i+1) #   ,     
        
    else:
        return res_dict

def ploting(result_dict, title):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    fig.suptitle(title)
    ax.set_xlabel(' ')
    ax.set_ylabel('')
    ax.plot(result_dict.items())
    ax.legend(['(y)', '(dn)'])
    
def visual(dict): 
    list = [i for i in enumerate(dict.items())]
    for i in list[:5]: print(' : %d \n(y), (dn) \n%s' % i)
    print('\n...\n')
    for i in list[-5:]: print(' : %d \n(y), (dn) \n%s' % i)
    return None

In [25]:
res_dict2 = {}

def train2(start_w, dd2=0.01, i=1):
    x2 = start_w[0] * start_x #    2- 
    y2 = activation(x2) #    2- 
    
    x3 = start_w[1] * y2 #    3- 
    y3 = activation(x3) #    3- 
    
    dn = abs((res - y3)/res) #  
    res_dict2[y3] = dn
    
    if dn > dd2: #  
        q3 = y3 * (1 - y3) * (res - y3)
        q2 = y2 * (1 - y2) * (q3 * start_w[1])
        
        delta_23 = q3 * y2 #    2- 
        delta_12 = q2 * start_x #    1- 
        
        w_23 = start_w[1] + delta_23 #  
        w_12 = start_w[0] + delta_12 
        return train2(np.array([w_12, w_23]), i=i+1) #   ,  
                                                     #  dn > dd2   
    else: 
        return start_w
    
w_test2 = train2(start_w)
    
def test2(start):
    return (activation(activation(start * w_test2[0]) *w_test2[1]))

In [32]:
res_dict3 = {}

def train3(middle_w, final_w, i=0):
    input_xs = np.array([1, *input_x])
    x1 = sum_of_weigths(input_xs, middle_w[0]) #    1   
    y1 = activation(x1) #    1   
    
    x2 = sum_of_weigths(input_xs, middle_w[1])   
    y2 = activation(x2)
    
    x3 = sum_of_weigths(input_xs, middle_w[2]) 
    y3 = activation(x3)
    
    ys = np.array([y1, y2, y3])
    
    X = final_w[0] * input_xs[0] + sum_of_weigths(final_w[1:], ys) #     
    Y = activation(X) #      
     
    dn = abs((result - Y)/result)
    #print(' dn: ', dn)
    res_dict3[Y] = dn
    if dn > dd3:
        q1_3 = Y * (1 - Y) * (result - Y) #   
        
        b_01_2 = q1_3 * input_xs[0] #  
        b_11_2 = q1_3 * y1
        b_21_2 = q1_3 * y2
        b_31_2 = q1_3 * y3
        
        w_i1_2 = final_w + np.array([b_01_2,  b_11_2, b_21_2, b_31_2]) #    
      
        '''  1-  ,   1- 1 '''
        q1_2 = y1 * (1 - y1) * (q1_3 * final_w[1]) #    
        
        b_i1_1 = q1_2 * input_xs #   
        
        w_i1_1 = middle_w[0] + b_i1_1 #    1-  
        
        '''    2-x  '''
        
        '''  2-  ,   2- 1 '''
        q2_2 = y2 * (1 - y2) * (q1_3 * final_w[2])
        
        b_i2_1 = q2_2 * input_xs
        
        w_i2_1 = middle_w[1] + b_i2_1
        
        '''  3-  ,   3- 1 '''
        q3_2 = y3 * (1 - y3) * (q1_3 * final_w[3])
        
        b_i3_1 = q3_2 * input_xs 
        
        w_i3_1 = middle_w[2] + b_i3_1
        
        return train3(np.array([[*w_i1_1],
                                [*w_i2_1], 
                                [*w_i3_1]]), w_i1_2, i = i+1)
    else:
        return middle_w, final_w
    
w_test3 = train3(middle_W, final_W)
                 
def test3(data_test3):
    prop = np.array([1, *data_test3])
    sec_l1 = activation(sum_of_weigths(prop, w_test3[0][0]))
    sec_l2 = activation(sum_of_weigths(prop, w_test3[0][1]))
    sec_l3 = activation(sum_of_weigths(prop, w_test3[0][2]))
    
    prop_last = np.array([1, sec_l1, sec_l2, sec_l3])
    res = activation(sum_of_weigths(prop_last,  w_test3[1] ))
    return res
